# YYR4 Linux Control Udev Rules
#
# This rule grants access to the YYR4 device's input event nodes for the currently 
# active local session user via systemd-logind's 'uaccess' tag.
# 
# NOTE: 
# - This rule only matches the event nodes. It does not grant read/write permissions
#   to the entire USB device or to inactive sessions.
# - The yyr4-linux-control daemon is responsible for identity parsing and role selection.
# - If you are not using systemd-logind or an equivalent seat manager, this rule
#   will not automatically grant you access.
# - We explicitly avoid 0666 modes or input groups to maintain strict security boundaries.

SUBSYSTEM=="input", KERNEL=="event*", ATTRS{idVendor}=="239a", ATTRS{idProduct}=="80f4", TAG+="uaccess"
